\begin{document}$$ \frac{{{\text{d}}A_{2} }} {{{\text{d}}t}} = B \cdot k_{{\text{a}}}  \cdot A_{1}  - k_{{{\text{el}}}}  \cdot A_{2}$$\end{document}Here A2 is the amount of hGH present in serum and kel is the elimination rate constant. Finally, the serum hGH concentration followed from dividing this amount by the average distribution volume (Vd) of the elderly male human volunteers (70  ml/kg body weight). The in vitro in vivo correlation was evaluated by comparing the calculated serum concentration time data to the measured serum concentration time data.
